author_ssm: Jane Gorzhevskaya, Fall 1997. Collection reprocessed by Emily King, 2014.
unittitle_ssm: Pleiades Club Collection
abstract_ssm: The Pleiades Club was a Greenwich Village literary society of the early 20th century. Howard Neiman was a member of the Board of Governors throughout the Club's history, and served in other posts at the Club. The collection includes Neiman's club correspondence and printed items which illuminate aspects of the literary and artistic life of the Village of that time.
